Kenya faces a plastic bag crisis, with millions discarded annually.
The United Nations Environment Programme calls for a ban and hefty levies to combat the environmental and health risks.
Plastic bags harm wildlife, pollute soil, and increase malaria risk.
Eritrea and Rwanda have already taken steps to ban plastic bags.
In Uganda, a 50% excise duty failed to reduce usage, prompting consideration of a total ban.
Tanzania plans to establish a recycling plant to address plastic waste.
Across Africa, governments are taking action to combat the menace of plastic bags and protect the environment.
